edu.uidaho.junicon.runtime.junicon.operators

Class UniconFunctions

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.uidaho.junicon.runtime.junicon.operators.UniconFunctions

  • public class UniconFunctions
extends Object
    Defines the built-in Unicon functions. The built-in functions are exposed as method references.

    USAGE: When compiling to Java: import static UniconFunctions.*;

    • Method Detail

      • flush

        public static Object flush(Object... args)
        Flushes any accumulated output for file f. IMPLEMENTATION NOTE: currently write and writes always flush their output, since RandomAccessFile does not have a flush method and BufferedWriter is really only used for standard output, which should be flushed on every line written for the expected semantics.
        Returns:
        The number of bytes written

        Returns:

      • reads

        public static Object reads(Object... args)
        Produces a string consisting of the next i characters from f, or the remaining characters if fewer than i remain. Fails on end of file. f defaults to standard input, while i defaults to 1. USAGE: reads(f,i)
        Returns:
        A string of i or fewer characters

      • open

        public static Object open(Object... args)
        Produces a file resulting from opening the path p with options o. Fails if the file cannot be opened. Options for opening the file are: - "r": open for reading - "w": open for writing - "a": open for writing in append mode - "b": open for reading and writing - "p": open a pipe - "c": create - "t": translate line termination sequences to linefeeds - "u": do not translate line termination sequences to linefeeds - "o": opens a SQL database connection The default mode is to translate line termination sequences to linefeeds on input, and vice-versa on output. USAGE: open(p,o)
        Returns:
        The opened file, or fail.

      • seek

        public static Object seek(Object... args)
        Seeks to position i in file f. Fails if the seek cannot be performed. The first byte in the file is at position 1. i = 0 seeks to the end of the file.
        Parameters:
        args -
